<div id="main_content">
	<h2>UCF Global Perspectives Office Hosting Conference on Future of Europe</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Sam Gardner
		
		<span class="date">Nov. 9, 2006</span></p>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
		
			<div id="related">
				<h3>Related Contacts and Links:</h3>
				<ul>
		
		<li>
		
			
				<h4><a href="mailto:sridley@mail.ucf.edu">Sarah Ridley, Global Perspectives</a></h4>
			
			
			
				<ul>
				<li>407-823-0935</li>
			
			</ul>
		
		</li>
	
		
		<li>
		
			
				<h4><a href="mailto:cbinette@mail.ucf.edu">Chad Binette, News & Information</a></h4>
			
			
			
				<ul>
				<li>407-823-6312</li>
			
			</ul>
		
		</li>
	
	
	
		
		<li>
		
			<h4><a href="http://www.ucfglobalperspectives.org">UCF Global Perspectives Office</a></h4>
		
		</li>
	
	
	 </ul></div> 
	
	
			
	
	
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	<div id="share">
		<ul><li><p id="print"><a href="javascript:window.print();">Print this Page</a></li></ul>
	
	</div>
	
	
	
	
		
			<p><country-region /><place />U.S.</place /></country-region /> and foreign government officials will join university professors and newspaper editors Monday, Nov. 13, at a daylong conference on The Future of Europe: The Ties That Bind &amp; Divide at the <place /><placetype />University</placetype /> of <placename />Central Florida</placename /></place />. </p><p>The conference will be hosted by the UCF Global Perspectives Office, which is focusing on <place />Europe</place /> during the 2006-07 academic year. The conference, held in conjunction with the National Conference of Editorial Writers, will be from 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. at the Fairwinds Alumni Center. </p><p>Gerard Baker, the <country-region /><place />United States</place /></country-region /> editor of <i>The Times</i> in <city /><place />London</place /></city />, will give the morning keynote address at <time hour="9" minute="15" />9:15 a.m.</time /> </p><p>After Bakers speech, a panel moderated by Jonathan Gurwitz of the San Antonio Express-News on Transatlantic Cooperation and Conflict will convene. The panel will feature Kurt Volker, principal deputy assistant secretary for European and Eurasian Affairs for the U.S. State Department, and David Houghton, an assistant professor of political science at UCF. </p><p>A keynote luncheon from <time hour="12" minute="0" />noon</time /> to <time hour="13" minute="30" />1:30 p.m.</time /> will feature Mabel Gonzalez Bustelo of Centro de Investigación para <city /><place />la Paz</place /></city /> (Center for the Investigation of Peace) in <place /><city />Madrid</city />, <country-region />Spain</country-region /></place />. Bustelo will talk about the 2004 <state /><place />Madrid</place /></state /> bombings and their impact on <place />Europe</place />. </p><p>Stephen Sloan, a professor and coordinator of the Terrorism Studies Program at UCF, will headline a panel on security and terrorism. He will be joined by speakers from the British Embassy in Washington, D.C., and the Institute for Transitional Democracy and International Security in Budapest, Hungary. </p><p>The event will conclude with a panel on Democracy-building, Corruption &amp; Other Challenges with professors from UCF and Stetson, Tim Cullen from the Said Business School at Oxford University in Oxford, England, and Angelos Pangratis from the European Commissions Delegation to the United States. Harriet L. Elam-Thomas, director of the Diplomacy Program at UCF, will moderate that panel. </p><p>Telephone or e-mail registrations will be accepted through Sunday, Nov. 12. To register, call 407-823-0935 or e-mail <a href="mailto:sridley@mail.ucf.edu">sridley@mail.ucf.edu </a>. The cost is $95 per person and may be paid on the day of the conference. The registration fee includes refreshments, lunch, conference materials and a one-day parking pass. </p><p>Sponsors of the conference are the Orlando Sentinel, the Global Connections Foundation and UCFs Political Science Department, European Studies Program, <place /><placename />International</placename /> <placename />Services</placename /> <placetype />Center</placetype /></place /> and Nicholson School of Communication. </p><p>For a full conference schedule, go to <a href="http://www.ucfglobalperspectives.org/">www.ucfglobalperspectives.org</a>.</p>
		
	
